It is marked as a factory test fire (from the Kahr website: Q. What does the "U" on the trigger guard of my pistol mean? A. If there is a "U" engraved on the trigger guard of your pistol, it is a factory refurbished and test fired model (often sold as a "test fired" gun). From what I understand, Kahr pulls some assembled pistols off the assembly line, fires them and marks them as a factory test fire.
